    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="624"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d624">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 365.117/34a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        Ambassador <persName type="to">Page</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-06">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 6, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. Your 34, October 2, concerning detention naturalized American citizens in
                    Italy. In absence of naturalization treaty all you can do is to express
                    earnestly this Government’s interest in persons concerned and desire for their
                    release, especially in view of destitute condition, in most cases, of their
                    families here. Emphasize fact that this Government is interested only in bona
                    fide citizens and not in those who have expatriated themselves by protracted
                    residence abroad or whose naturalization was procured in bad faith.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
